Caleb Chase.about:
I started this album probably 3-4 years ago but it always felt unfinished. I slowly changed certain things, added and subtracted layers, rewrote lyrics and re-recorded vocals but it never felt done and the rougher more sketchy recordings I began with felt more genuine. The further away I get from the original recordings the more detached I feel to them and changing them at this point feels wrong. So the earlier rougher recordings are mostly whats here.
Recorded on 4-track cassette in rooms in Allston, Jamaica Plain, Somerville, Royalston, and Worcester.

All instruments and recordings done by me.

Recorded mostly on 4-track with some digital post production in my bedroom in Worcester, MA. Recorded probably mostly between Autumn 2020 and Winter 2022.

trackinfo.title: Hibernaculum
trackinfo.lyrics: in late fall leaves create blankets across the ground the last few leaves are all falling down one last gust of wind to blow them off and set them free to become the food for which little worms and bugs will eat and soon the ground will freeze and snow will cover fallen leaves and forest creatures all around will rest in holes in the ground birds and butterflies travel south as bears and rodents gorge their mouths with nuts and berries, stems and seeds to prepare for a winters sleep and then some day in spring suns warmth will cover everything and creatures will emerge from their homes to see the little flowers grow snows will melt, warm rains will fall as amphibians will crawl into puddles, pools and streams as the world turns from brown to green

trackinfo.title: Porcupine
trackinfo.lyrics: porcupine, porcupine your bodys covered in little spines i see you eating pears up in the tree oh wont you come eat fruits with me porcupine dont be scared no need to raise your prickly hairs i just want to eat pears with thee way up in the branches of the old pear tree

trackinfo.title: Flying in Vs
trackinfo.lyrics: sometimes i look up to the sky see clouds, geese flying by they travel in vs to escape the cold winter freeze until they reach a place to fill their bellies squawking and gawking as the world passes below and when spring comes around talons leave the ground traveling north til their homes again found where theyll lay their heads and their young will be fed safe from the predators of their winter 'sted
